public class IntradayThruConnector<S extends Securitycurrency<S>> extends BaseIntradayThru<S>
Intraday price updater that retrieves real-time market data through external feed connectors.

This class handles intraday price updates for securities and currency pairs by interfacing with external data providers through configured feed connectors. It provides comprehensive functionality including:

  • Feed Connector Management: Locates and validates appropriate connectors based on entity configuration
  • Retry Logic: Implements sophisticated retry mechanisms with configurable limits and automatic counter management
  • Delayed Update Control: Respects data provider delay requirements and timeout constraints
  • Secure Link Generation: Creates download links with proper API key protection and routing
  • Entity-Specific Processing: Handles both Security and Currencypair entities with appropriate connector methods

  • Method Details

    • updateLastPriceSecurityCurrency

      public S updateLastPriceSecurityCurrency(S securitycurrency, short maxIntraRetry, int scIntradayUpdateTimeout)
      Description copied from interface: IIntradayLoad
      Updates intraday price of a single security or currency pair with comprehensive validation and error handling.

      This method performs a complete update cycle including:

      • Feed connector validation based on idConnectorIntra and FS_INTRA support
      • Retry limit checking against the security's current retryIntraLoad counter
      • Active status verification using isActiveForIntradayUpdate()
      • Delayed update allowance based on connector's intradayDelayedSeconds and last update timestamp
      • Automatic retry counter management (reset on success, increment on failure)
      • Database persistence of updated security state

      Parameters:
      securitycurrency - the security or currency pair to update
      maxIntraRetry - maximum number of retry attempts for failed price updates, -1 for unlimited retries
      scIntradayUpdateTimeout - timeout in seconds for determining if delayed updates are allowed
      Returns:
      the security with updated intraday price and persisted retry counter, or original security if update was skipped

    • getSecuritycurrencyIntraDownloadLinkAsUrlStr

      public String getSecuritycurrencyIntraDownloadLinkAsUrlStr(S securitycurrency)
      Description copied from interface: IIntradayLoad
      Generates a download link URL string for intraday data with intelligent lazy loading detection.

      Creates a URL for retrieving intraday price data by first locating the appropriate feed connector based on the security's idConnectorIntra. The method intelligently determines the link type:

      • Returns "lazy" if the connector supports DL_LAZY_INTRA (lazy loading)
      • Otherwise delegates to createDownloadLink() for immediate link generation
      • Returns null if no suitable feed connector is found

      Parameters:
      securitycurrency - the security or currency pair for which to generate the download link
      Returns:
      URL string for accessing intraday data, "lazy" for lazy-loaded connectors, or null if no connector available

    • createDownloadLink

      public String createDownloadLink(S securitycurrency, IFeedConnector feedConnector)
      Description copied from interface: IIntradayLoad
      Creates a download link with API key security and connector-specific routing logic.

      Generates download links with sophisticated security and routing logic:

      • For accessible API keys and non-DL_INTRA_FORCE_BACKEND connectors: creates direct provider links
      • For Security entities: uses feedConnector.getSecurityIntradayDownloadLink()
      • For Currencypair entities: uses feedConnector.getCurrencypairIntradayDownloadLink()
      • For protected API keys or DL_INTRA_FORCE_BACKEND: routes through secure backend using getDownlinkWithApiKey()

      Parameters:
      securitycurrency - the security or currency pair for which to create the download link
      feedConnector - the feed connector to use for link generation and API key access determination
      Returns:
      download link string (direct provider URL or secure backend-routed URL), or null if connector is null
